10/04/2011
PARIS, France -- Serbia and France signed a political partnership agreement in Paris on Friday (April 8th). Presidents Boris Tadic and Nicolas Sarkozy initialled the document, which stresses the importance of completing Serbia's EU accession talks. Tadic said his visit may be a turning point in bilateral relations. He says the deal includes tasks Serbia should fulfil in its European integration process. This partnership also envisions reforming the administration and co-operation in the fields of defence and infrastructure. Sarkozy said France will be the "best advocate" of Serbia's EU bid. (RTS, B92, Beta, Tanjug - 08/04/11)
